******
[1]
Date: Fri 16 Jul 2010
Source: Kyodo News International via istockanalyst.com [edited]
<http://www.istockanalyst.com/article/viewiStockNews/articleid/4313879>


Owner of stud bulls in Miyazaki accepts their slaughter
-------------------------------------------------------
The owner of 6 stud bulls, subjects of a recent dispute in Miyazaki
Prefecture, agreed Friday [16 Jul 2010] to slaughter them in order to
contain a foot-and-mouth disease [FMD] epidemic in the southwestern
Japanese prefecture, reversing his earlier opposition to the killing.

The owner accepted the precautionary measure at his meeting with
Miyazaki Gov. Hideo Higashikokubaru. His decision puts an end to the
twists and turns since late June [2010] over the fate of the 6
remaining bulls that need to be culled after some 289 000 cows and
pigs had been killed by the end of June.

--
